The compiler keeps the quoted names and renames everything else. If you remove the 
quotes around beer, the compiler won't break your code.

window.a = {
    beer: function() {
        print("beer was called");
    }
};
window.a.beer();

For further details see the tutorial at http://code.google.com/closure/compiler/docs/api-tutorial3.html#propnames
